special_notes: Full rules: Massachusetts allows both the use of zero (0) and the letter (O) in their plates. Any Diagonals are keyed up to the first three, but the plate can only be 7 characters long including prefixes or suffixes. Vertical characters are keyed as seen. Stickers are not keyed.
